# Storage and git (MaizeView)

## Durability (thin port of publisher tiers)

| Tier | Where | What belongs here |
|------|--------|-------------------|
| **1 — GitHub** | This repo | Code, `docs/`, rules, migrations, plans — **commit verified work often** |
| **2 — Outside repo** | User scan paths / libraries | Actual video files — never git-add media libraries |
| **3 — Local volatile** | Desktop NVMe, `%APPDATA%/MaizeView/` | Dev DB, thumbs cache, unlocked rebuilds — recreatable |

Portable product decisions live in **git** (`docs/plan.md`, `docs/decisions.md`, `docs/progress.md`). User media stays on **their disks**.

Shared publisher checklist: `publisher-config/PORTABILITY.md`. inn-roads Comfy/NAS rules **do not apply** here.

## Gitignore (do not fight)

- `src-tauri/lib/` — libmpv DLLs (re-fetch via setup-lib)
- `e2e/.env`, `e2e/.data/`, Playwright reports
- `docs/e2e-reports/*.png`
- `.env` / secrets

## Commits

- Commit verified work without waiting to be asked (matches user git policy).
- Push only when asked. Never force-push `main`.
- Gate: `cargo check` + `npm run build`; UI → E2E smoke when practical.
- No secrets, no DLLs, no personal library paths in commits.

## “Update the docs”

Update **`docs/progress.md`** (and plan/ADR if needed). Not an inn-roads `state.json` sync.
